We're one of a few communities that are paying such a heavy fee to have bus transportation, which is great.

213
00:18:25,438 --> 00:18:26,421
I like John Falco.

214
00:18:27,057 --> 00:18:28,378
take the bus every day also.

215
00:18:29,118 --> 00:18:35,881
But I can tell you, Mr. President, the access that we get in this community is not just for Method residents.

216
00:18:36,361 --> 00:18:48,107
We're paying a hefty fee to make sure people from all surrounding communities that jump on our express bus and all the other transit methods that we have, we're paying for their ridership as well, Mr. President.

217
00:18:48,567 --> 00:18:55,270
And I think, really, we need to make sure that the MBTA sees fit to make sure this community is getting its fair share.

218
00:18:56,121 --> 00:18:56,962
Thank you, Mr. Vice president.

219
00:18:56,982 --> 00:18:57,542
Counselor Knight.

220
00:18:57,982 --> 00:18:58,483
Mr. President.

221
00:18:58,523 --> 00:18:58,723
Yes.

222
00:18:58,783 --> 00:19:02,725
Also where the MBTA is a quasi public agency underneath the mass dot umbrella.

223
00:19:02,765 --> 00:19:06,988
I think it will be appropriate to amend the paper further and ask that this also be sent to a state delegation.

224
00:19:07,008 --> 00:19:08,829
So they're aware of the request that the council's making.

225
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:10,070
Thank you.

