Seven in the affirmative, none in the negative, motion passes.

247
00:20:15,769 --> 00:20:26,351
17-780 offered by Councilor Locker, be it resolved that the administration through the Energy and Environment Office develop a database and start an opt-out list for those who want to opt out

248
00:20:26,727 --> 00:20:31,430
of any potentially implemented community aggregation plans.

249
00:20:31,990 --> 00:20:33,010
Councilor Lungo-Kern.

250
00:20:33,671 --> 00:20:35,292
Thank you, President Carviello.

251
00:20:35,312 --> 00:20:40,955
I think the council in the last year or so has learned a great deal about community aggregation.

252
00:20:41,035 --> 00:20:53,762
We've had a number of meetings relating to it, and we also have had a very informative meeting back, I believe, in September with the energy environment director in Melrose, which I think,

253
00:20:55,748 --> 00:20:59,530
personally, for me, helped answer a lot of my questions.

254
00:20:59,570 --> 00:21:03,652
And it was great to see another community and how the plan is succeeding.

255
00:21:03,672 --> 00:21:15,819
I think one concern I do have is just Medford's ability to notify people of their rights and the ability to opt out.

256
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:22,143
And when I do get emails or phone calls or people stop me in the street to talk about community aggregation, 80% want to

257
00:21:24,591 --> 00:21:27,773
move forward with it and implement it in the city of Medford.

258
00:21:27,874 --> 00:21:51,372
But there are some, a good 20% if I, just going off the people that contact me, there are people that don't want government telling them what to do, what plan to go into, and they too are concerned that this 30-day opt-out, when it does become available, if potentially the council is to vote for it, there's just many concerns.

259
00:21:51,392 --> 00:21:54,074
They want to make sure that that opt-out plan is

260
00:21:54,781 --> 00:22:00,886
well publicized, and people know how to do it, and where to go, and who to talk to, who to ask questions to.

261
00:22:00,906 --> 00:22:04,750
And one resident brought this up to me, and we discussed it in depth.

262
00:22:04,870 --> 00:22:21,224
What if an opt-out plan was implemented, just even a database, a list of people that would relieve some of the 20% that I'm calculating from the people that I talk to, relieve them of their fears, and let them know that, no, we're not going to hide the fact that you can opt out.

263
00:22:22,421 --> 00:22:26,644
If you want to, you can do it now, just in case something is implemented.

264
00:22:27,224 --> 00:22:33,408
I know it's a reach, but it's something that was requested by a resident, and I don't think it's a bad idea.

265
00:22:33,428 --> 00:22:38,330
I think the community aggregation is something that we're going to talk about within the next several months.

266
00:22:39,011 --> 00:22:41,352
And we just need to be ready on all accounts.

267
00:22:41,552 --> 00:22:42,993
So I move this forward.

268
00:22:43,073 --> 00:22:45,455
I think it's definitely something worth exploring.

269
00:22:45,935 --> 00:22:46,555
It's simple.

270
00:22:46,655 --> 00:22:48,276
It's just a database.

271
00:22:48,336 --> 00:22:50,918
It could be an Excel spreadsheet of people that want to be

272
00:22:52,066 --> 00:23:13,943
listed as not being involved in this community aggregation from the get-go, and it would give a peace of mind to those who are not interested, and maybe it would help us get the votes, maybe unanimous, maybe not, but it would get votes to implement the plan, which I know a large percentage of Medford wants to work on and work towards.

273
00:23:14,863 --> 00:23:15,204
Thank you.

274
00:23:16,144 --> 00:23:16,885
Councilor Scott Pelli.

275
00:23:17,298 --> 00:23:18,419
Thank you, Mr. President.

276
00:23:18,459 --> 00:23:19,979
Thank you, my colleague, for bringing this forward.

277
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:35,928
I know that months and months and months ago when we first were presented, I was one of the councils that voted against it because of the lack of information that went out to our constituencies, to our community, and with the opt-out.

278
00:23:38,095 --> 00:23:52,085
in discussions with neighbors, where neighbors that have been very conscious about purchasing their own energy and they're valid in understanding what the situation was.

279
00:23:52,146 --> 00:23:59,431
And when I did my homework in visiting a few communities, one of the biggest pluses were

280
00:24:00,083 --> 00:24:14,993
The plan that was put in place once it was passed by each community, and the plan that notified our residents about the value of this process and the option of opting out.

281
00:24:15,113 --> 00:24:18,236
So one other thing that I want to point out,

282
00:24:18,976 --> 00:24:29,078
question that came about was who would fund the notifications, all of the work that needed to be done to let all of our residents know about the opt-out.

283
00:24:29,678 --> 00:24:42,621
And with our last meeting and having the director from Melrose who came in and spoke so well on this issue, we answered a lot of questions that were brought to my attention that people had

284
00:24:43,521 --> 00:24:46,543
asked me about and how would we find out who would pay.

285
00:24:47,004 --> 00:24:58,671
Well, it all comes under the company that would be awarded this project if and when it happens.

286
00:24:58,731 --> 00:25:08,336
So my biggest concern wasn't the community aggregation plan because I think it's needed.

287
00:25:08,356 --> 00:25:12,459
I think it's something that every

288
00:25:13,208 --> 00:25:17,351
constituent can use in bringing their electricity bill down.

289
00:25:17,391 --> 00:25:19,993
I mean, not dramatically, but it does help.

290
00:25:20,693 --> 00:25:25,837
And again, the biggest piece was getting the notification out to our residents.

291
00:25:26,477 --> 00:25:33,222
And I was pleasantly surprised and optimistic now in making sure that

292
00:25:33,982 --> 00:25:46,765
When that plan is released to the public, it's going to be very thorough and with as much information and time needed for our residents to opt out.

293
00:25:46,805 --> 00:25:50,786
Because again, one of the issues we often hear is a lack of notification.

294
00:25:51,206 --> 00:25:58,607
Well, with this plan, it falls back on the company that's awarded this project.

295
00:25:58,687 --> 00:26:02,248
So that in turn goes back out to our residents.

296
00:26:03,441 --> 00:26:08,705
I appreciate Councilor Longo-Curran for bringing this up, and I second her motion.

297
00:26:09,525 --> 00:26:10,686
Thank you, Councilor Scott-Bailey.

298
00:26:10,726 --> 00:26:11,326
Councilor Knight.

299
00:26:11,727 --> 00:26:13,108
Mr. President, thank you very much.

300
00:26:13,948 --> 00:26:18,071
When it comes to municipal aggregation, this is a topic that I think we've been discussing now for over a year.

301
00:26:18,671 --> 00:26:25,095
And quite frankly, the ball's in the council's court to determine whether or not this is something that we're going to allow the city to explore.

302
00:26:25,596 --> 00:26:28,057
And again, I think the time to move forward on it is now.

303
00:26:29,238 --> 00:26:30,699
Ultimately, the question is, do we want

304
00:26:31,209 --> 00:26:37,174
to request the department head to dedicate resources to something that hasn't been approved yet by this council.

305
00:26:37,394 --> 00:26:39,857
We're asking a department head to say, start creating a list.

306
00:26:40,057 --> 00:26:43,119
We may or may not adopt municipal aggregation.

307
00:26:43,660 --> 00:26:45,502
And I think we're putting the cart before the horse, Mr. President.

308
00:26:45,522 --> 00:26:48,244
If we want to explore municipal aggregation, let's explore municipal aggregation.

309
00:26:48,284 --> 00:26:49,805
Let's take the vote and let's allow it to happen.

310
00:26:51,647 --> 00:26:55,710
But to dedicate resources to something that may or may not happen, I don't feel comfortable doing that.

311
00:26:58,003 --> 00:27:01,164
the Director of Energy and Environment to start to begin to create an opt-out list.

312
00:27:02,204 --> 00:27:05,305
So she's going to dedicate resources in her office towards something that we may not adopt.

313
00:27:08,226 --> 00:27:11,527
So I think that this might be a little bit counterintuitive at this point in time.

314
00:27:11,547 --> 00:27:13,568
Mr. President, I'll have a difficult time supporting it this evening.

315
00:27:14,428 --> 00:27:14,768
Thank you.

316
00:27:16,249 --> 00:27:17,009
Councilor Falco.

317
00:27:17,229 --> 00:27:18,549
Thank you, Mr. President.

318
00:27:20,330 --> 00:27:24,471
As many of you know, I've been on board with municipal aggregation since day one.

319
00:27:25,051 --> 00:27:27,292
I think it's a good, in my eyes, I think it's a good

320
00:27:28,021 --> 00:27:29,562
a good plan, I think it's a good program.

321
00:27:30,722 --> 00:27:43,087
And I, I too think that, you know, we're at the point now where, you know, I think we've heard from, you know, you know, at the last meeting we heard from someone from the energy department in Melrose just to get a different perspective.

322
00:27:43,107 --> 00:27:44,908
And I think, I thought that was a very good presentation.

323
00:27:44,948 --> 00:27:50,650
She did a great job and it was good to see how another city handled the communication and how they worked through the project.

324
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:53,831
And she had all kinds of samples of communications that they sent out.

325
00:27:54,589 --> 00:27:57,513
But I, in fact, I also agree with the Councilor Knight.

326
00:27:57,573 --> 00:28:01,978
I think we need to take a vote on this to see where we're going.

327
00:28:02,318 --> 00:28:06,322
You know, I mean, I would, I guess I feel the same way.

328
00:28:06,342 --> 00:28:09,806
I mean, I don't want to put resources working on something that might not even pass.

329
00:28:09,826 --> 00:28:12,269
So, you know, I think, you know, it's time.

330
00:28:12,742 --> 00:28:16,263
This has been, I think municipal aggregation has been with us for over a year now.

331
00:28:16,563 --> 00:28:24,786
We've had many meetings, Committee of the Wholes, we've taken one vote, it went down, and it's come back, but I think we need to take a vote on this.

332
00:28:25,207 --> 00:28:32,409
And I know, I think the paper is still in committee, or actually it's in Committee of the Wholes, so I think we probably need to vote that out at some point.

333
00:28:32,489 --> 00:28:39,792
But I think that, in my opinion, I really don't, I think a lot of our

334
00:28:40,322 --> 00:28:42,422
departments to stretch with regard to resources.

335
00:28:42,482 --> 00:28:50,564
And I would, I really don't, um, like the fact that we're going to put a resource towards building this list if this might not even pass.

336
00:28:50,804 --> 00:28:55,625
So, um, I, I, uh, agree with my colleague, uh, councilor Knight on this issue.

337
00:28:55,665 --> 00:28:56,365
So thank you.

338
00:28:56,885 --> 00:28:57,265
Thank you.

339
00:28:57,946 --> 00:28:58,906
Councilor DelaRusso.

340
00:28:59,186 --> 00:29:00,266
Thank you, Mr. President.

341
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:09,388
Um, every presentation we've had on this matter from the office of energy and environment, which has been, they've been excellent presentations.

342
00:29:10,017 --> 00:29:13,999
It's quite clear to me that the Office of Energy and Environment has an agenda.

343
00:29:14,539 --> 00:29:18,180
Their agenda is to get METFIT into municipal aggregation.

344
00:29:18,701 --> 00:29:26,324
And so every presentation we've had has told us how wonderful and awesome and stupendous of an idea this is.

345
00:29:27,124 --> 00:29:36,968
And maybe indeed it is, but we haven't had one credible, balanced presentation of what the negatives are with it, Mr. President.

346
00:29:37,428 --> 00:29:39,789
And a lot of people are concerned about that in the community.

347
00:29:40,404 --> 00:29:46,449
A lot of people think that it would be a good idea that we have, rather than an opt out, an opt in.

348
00:29:46,870 --> 00:29:55,718
So the city offers it, and if people in the community want to do that and get together and do it, then they should opt in.

349
00:29:56,238 --> 00:30:03,885
Now obviously the vendors have something to benefit from by getting the greater portion of the community involved in this.

350
00:30:04,626 --> 00:30:05,787
They have something to gain.

351
00:30:06,460 --> 00:30:11,222
Obviously, always someone has something to gain, and there's nothing wrong with that.

352
00:30:12,323 --> 00:30:24,549
I think this is a stretch in some areas, and I'm particularly concerned, Mr. President, that we'd create a list in advance of people who don't want to participate in this, who don't want to be a member of this.

353
00:30:24,629 --> 00:30:25,809
What does this do to them?

354
00:30:26,229 --> 00:30:27,750
Does this target them in some way?

355
00:30:27,810 --> 00:30:29,431
Who has an access to this list?

356
00:30:29,878 --> 00:30:34,261
Are they going to be contacted and given a spiel to get them to come aboard?

357
00:30:34,281 --> 00:30:38,784
Um, these are questions, uh, serious questions that I have.

358
00:30:39,225 --> 00:30:44,548
These are serious questions that people in the community have, Mr. President, that they need a voice as well.

359
00:30:45,069 --> 00:30:46,570
I'm going to give them that voice.

360
00:30:47,090 --> 00:30:49,652
And so I do not support this motion, Mr. President.

361
00:30:50,192 --> 00:30:53,895
I think we need to have further discussion on municipal, uh, aggregation.

362
00:30:54,275 --> 00:30:56,797
And I think we need to have a credible,

363
00:30:57,338 --> 00:31:03,759
bona fide expert on this matter who is going to give the argument contra.

364
00:31:04,460 --> 00:31:05,480
Thank you, Mr. President.

365
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:06,980
Thank you, Mr. Counselor.

366
00:31:07,660 --> 00:31:08,560
Counselor Lugo-Curran.

367
00:31:09,401 --> 00:31:11,981
Thank you, President Carviello.

368
00:31:12,101 --> 00:31:15,242
I understand the sentiments of my colleagues.

369
00:31:15,402 --> 00:31:19,023
I just, I don't feel, I have to just speak again on it, I guess.

370
00:31:19,063 --> 00:31:24,524
I don't feel that it would take a great amount of resources to start an Excel spreadsheet and people

371
00:31:25,086 --> 00:31:28,707
call or write in, shoot a quick email to say they want to be on the opt-out list.

372
00:31:28,827 --> 00:31:34,790
I actually think that it would ease a lot of people's fears, those that definitely do not want to be part of this.

373
00:31:35,330 --> 00:31:37,251
I think it's simple, take minutes.

374
00:31:37,771 --> 00:31:53,077
And I agree with Councilor DelaRusso, there is an agenda for the Office of Environment and Energy, but I don't think that that's what the people are concerned about, that the agenda won't be notifying people accordingly on their

375
00:31:53,610 --> 00:32:03,676
option to opt out, how many days they have to do it, and the fact that they can opt out whenever, they're going to be put in if they don't opt out within that first 30 days.

376
00:32:03,816 --> 00:32:05,497
And that's what people are concerned about.

377
00:32:05,597 --> 00:32:20,385
So that's why you would implement something like this far beforehand, and you would be able to create that list, and people would be able to say, I want to opt out, and they would get what they want.

378
00:32:20,425 --> 00:32:21,826
The people that don't want to be involved

379
00:32:22,193 --> 00:32:24,374
would be able to do that sooner than later.

380
00:32:24,514 --> 00:32:29,877
And when the council does meet in committee of the whole again, maybe there would be the definite votes for it.

381
00:32:29,897 --> 00:32:31,738
And I think we're definitely close to it.

382
00:32:31,818 --> 00:32:34,820
And I know people have definitely changed their minds.

383
00:32:34,900 --> 00:32:36,341
And they've learned a lot.

384
00:32:36,381 --> 00:32:38,402
There are some people that maybe are still against it.

385
00:32:38,462 --> 00:32:44,566
But for me, this is something that would make me feel a whole lot better knowing that they have more than that 30 days.

386
00:32:45,286 --> 00:32:48,008
Because that's the complaints I've been getting.

387
00:32:48,048 --> 00:32:49,849
And I thought this was just a way

388
00:32:51,806 --> 00:32:56,210
sway another vote towards approving it and ease in people's fears.

389
00:32:56,411 --> 00:32:57,051
I'll say it again.

390
00:32:57,412 --> 00:32:59,134
So I move approval.

391
00:32:59,234 --> 00:33:01,716
I'd like to see how it goes.

392
00:33:01,937 --> 00:33:06,441
And of course, we'll be meeting on it again in Committee of the Whole, probably after the holidays.

393
00:33:07,002 --> 00:33:08,003
Thank you, Councilor Locario.

394
00:33:08,344 --> 00:33:09,285
Vice President Mox.

395
00:33:10,145 --> 00:33:11,087
Thank you, Mr. President.

396
00:33:12,072 --> 00:33:19,880
I can't support this resolution tonight based on the fact that I agree with my colleagues that this is something that hasn't been approved by the council as of yet.

397
00:33:20,641 --> 00:33:28,249
And I'm not going to partake in something that is going to tell residents that they can get out of something that the council is going to vote on.

398
00:33:29,050 --> 00:33:31,873
Um, and in my opinion, what we should do,

399
00:33:32,492 --> 00:33:44,879
and I've stated this from day one, Mr. President is, uh, the energy and environment committee where this was sent at one point in this process, um, had a public hearing on it and we asked the city solicitor to attend.

400
00:33:45,499 --> 00:33:59,126
And one of the questions, and it was actually my question was whether or not we can file a home rule petition on behalf of this city and change the legislation, which, uh, is everyone is opted into the program.

401
00:34:00,106 --> 00:34:00,347
And, um,

402
00:34:01,969 --> 00:34:07,918
automatically and change it so you can opt into the program.

403
00:34:09,540 --> 00:34:15,709
And according to Mark Rumley, and I don't want to put words in his mouth, he spoke to House Counsel

404
00:34:16,856 --> 00:34:21,161
at the statehouse and they believe that we could file a home loan petition.

405
00:34:21,641 --> 00:34:23,403
And that is my number one concern.

406
00:34:24,564 --> 00:34:35,656
In my opinion, when you get into utilities, that's between a homeowner and the utility company, not between the homeowner, the utility company, and the city of Meffitt.

407
00:34:36,056 --> 00:34:39,759
I don't think we have any business getting involved, to be quite honest with you.

408
00:34:40,139 --> 00:34:45,504
I realize this is a good intention to reduce our carbon footprint.

409
00:34:45,984 --> 00:34:51,669
I realize that supposedly there's a cost benefit to by aggregating everyone together.

410
00:34:52,289 --> 00:34:55,752
And so I realize what the intent is.

411
00:34:56,313 --> 00:35:03,078
But I, as one member of the council, don't feel that everyone should be opted in automatically to a program.

412
00:35:03,879 --> 00:35:05,380
And if this is such a great program,

413
00:35:06,121 --> 00:35:07,122
It's going to be overwhelming.

414
00:35:07,182 --> 00:35:13,085
People will be knocking on the door here at City Hall to get involved and say, I want to opt into that program.

415
00:35:13,866 --> 00:35:15,107
Let the program work.

416
00:35:15,707 --> 00:35:16,648
Let the program work.

417
00:35:16,968 --> 00:35:18,649
So that would be my recommendation.

418
00:35:19,005 --> 00:35:29,647
Mr. President, that eventually, when we do discuss this again, that we file a home rule petition to reverse it, Mr. President, because the state legislature made a mistake, in my opinion.

419
00:35:30,368 --> 00:35:31,408
Maybe it wasn't a mistake.

